Privacy Policy – Rays’s Restaurant Bot

Last Updated: March 1, 2026

Your privacy is important. This Privacy Policy explains what information Rays’s Restaurant Bot (the “Bot”) collects, how it is used, and your rights. By using the Bot, you agree to this policy.

1. Information We Collect

The Bot may collect the following information to function properly on your Discord server:

User Information: Discord usernames, user IDs, join dates, and roles.

Server Information: Channel IDs, role IDs, and server IDs where the Bot operates.

Interactions: Messages deleted with /clear, command usage logs, and any avatars accessed via /rob.

Optional Content: Any text, images, or input you provide directly through the Bot commands.

We do not collect sensitive information such as passwords, payment info, or personal private messages.

2. How We Use Information

We use collected data solely to:

Provide Bot functionality (moderation, fun commands, etc.).

Ensure commands respect role permissions.

Improve the Bot’s performance and fix bugs.

We do not sell, rent, or share your personal information with third parties for marketing.

3. Data Storage

Collected data is stored temporarily in memory or logs for command execution.

Sensitive or personal user data is not permanently stored.

Message deletions and command logs may be stored briefly for audit purposes but are not shared externally.

4. User Rights

You can request the removal of your data by contacting the Bot developer.

You can disable the Bot in your server at any time by removing it from the server.

5. Security

The Bot follows basic security practices to protect data during operation.

However, no method of transmission over the Internet or storage is 100% secure. Use the Bot responsibly.

6. Third-Party Links

The Bot may provide links (e.g., GitHub profile) but does not control third-party websites. We are not responsible for their privacy practices.

7. Changes to Privacy Policy

This policy may be updated. Continued use of the Bot after updates indicates acceptance of the new terms.
